KIESS — built on Evermeet ruins along Roc Road (ancient east-west trade artery).
Evermeet fell through decades of neglect, not one night. Kiess is replacement,
not restoration. "Evermeet remembered, but finally made defensible."

CENTRAL PRISM:
Continuity anchor from Evermeet's civic hall; city's practical + memorial hub
Law, messaging, provisioning, magical logistics all within steps
Executioner stationed here; violent breach answered immediately and publicly

THREE-POWER GOVERNANCE (no faction dominates; each holds a tribunal seat):
Compact Temples: sanctuary law, civic rites, Prism memorial; Temple of Concord
/ Shrine of the Compact Flame
Trade Syndics: caravan contracts, Roc Road commerce; Kowloon tariff talks
Wall Command: gate discipline, four watchtowers; scout debriefing posts
in north ring forward intelligence to Midgaard road wardens

ROC ROAD: East gate leads to Midgaard and the western frontier. Named for
"roc" mythology from Serathi hunting parties at altitude — travelers reporting
giant winged shapes were mostly seeing Serathi. Serathi sky-road records predate
Keeper surveys; Trade Syndics negotiating access to pre-Evermeet chronicles.

FOREST OF CONFUSION (north): Failed druidic quarantine merged with ancient
forest intelligence. Mist-fever: psychoactive disorientation, not weather;
onset sudden. Wall Command rope-lines + bell-posts through southern verge.
Healers process casualties in central wards.

WITHERED DEPTHS (deeper forest): Conclave crystal blight in root systems;
still propagating; scouts track it; reports forwarded to Midgaard.

CONCLAVE INHERITANCE: Obsidian disc (Conclave triune seal) found in foundation
excavations; confirms Evermeet's role in condemned-labor transfers. Founding
charter repudiates sealed warrants from predecessor authorities — written
directly in response. Compact Temples cite Forest + Withered Depths as
cautionary parables about unchecked institutional power.

White civic stone, blue-and-gold banners, prismatic glasswork.
